Sentencas: This study utilizes nanoindentation to investigate and measure creep properties of a barium calcium alumino-silicate glass-ceramic used for solid oxide fuel cell seals (SOFCs).
Titulo: Creep properties of solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic seal G18

Sentencas: Samples of the glass-ceramic seal material were aged for 5, 50, and 100 h to obtain different degrees of crystallinity.
Titulo: Creep properties of solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic seal G18

Sentencas: Instrumented nanoindentation was performed on the samples with different aging times at different temperatures to investigate the strain rate sensitivity during inelastic deformation.
Titulo: Creep properties of solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic seal G18

Sentencas: The temperature dependent behavior is important since SOFCs operate at high temperatures (800-1000 degrees C).
Titulo: Creep properties of solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic seal G18

Sentencas: Results show that the samples with higher crystallinity were more resistant to creep, and the creep compliance tended to decrease with increasing temperature, especially with further aged samples.
Titulo: Creep properties of solid oxide fuel cell glass-ceramic seal G18
